
Overview of noun inflection

The noun inflection has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                     
1. (1) inflection, inflexion -- (a change in the form of a word (usually by adding a suffix) to indicate a change in its grammatical function)
2. (1) prosody, inflection -- (the patterns of stress and intonation in a language)
3. inflection, flection, flexion -- (deviation from a straight or normal course)
4. modulation, inflection -- (a manner of speaking in which the loudness or pitch or tone of the voice is modified)
